<subSubSection pageId="92" pageNumber="93" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="92.[151,1437,387,954]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,639,665]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is a member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Malaise" authorityYear="1931" box="[678,763,639,665]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vafer">
<emphasis box="[678,763,639,665]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">P. vafer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex (Shinohara 2005) or the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Malaise" authorityYear="1931" box="[1143,1228,639,665]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vafer">
<emphasis box="[1143,1228,639,665]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">P. vafer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Malaise" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vafer">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">P. vafer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[293,489,675,701]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara 2002b</bibRefCitation>
), which is a complex of birch- or alder-feeding species having much in common morphologically and genetically (see also comments under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="2005" box="[774,907,711,737]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alnivorus">
<emphasis box="[774,907,711,737]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">P. alnivorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The larva of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="2005" box="[1074,1175,712,737]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masao">
<emphasis box="[1074,1175,712,737]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">P. masao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a solitary leaf-roller. The egg is laid on the upperside and the larval leaf-roll is also on the upperside of the leaf (
<typeStatus box="[1190,1247,747,773]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Type</typeStatus>
III of Shinohara 2005). This character is known otherwise only for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="2005" box="[721,847,783,809]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusus">
<emphasis box="[721,847,783,809]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">P. confusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="2005" box="[903,1052,783,809]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipectus">
<emphasis box="[903,1052,783,809]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">P. flavipectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1121,1185,784,810]" name="Japan" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Kojima, H." pageId="92" pageNumber="93" pagination="23 - 28" refId="ref78244" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Kojima, H. (2006) Some biological features of three Pamphilius species (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) feeding on alders in Nagano Prefecture, Honshu, Japan: Results of rearing experiments in 2004 / 2005. Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Tokyo, Series A, 32, 23 - 28." type="journal article" year="2006">Shinohara &amp; Kojima 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="92.[151,1437,387,954]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="2005" box="[199,409,855,881]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masao">
<emphasis box="[199,409,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Pamphilius masao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is fairly common in montane birch forests in 
